# API Routes & Server Actions Security

Specific security patterns for API endpoints and server actions with Clerk authentication.

## API Route Structure

### ✅ Standard Protected Route Template
```typescript
import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs';
import { db } from '@/db';
import { decks } from '@/db/schema';
import { eq, and } from 'drizzle-orm';

export async function GET() {
  // 1. Authentication check
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) {
    return Response.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 });
  }

  try {
    // 2. Data fetching with user filtering
    const userDecks = await db.select()
      .from(decks)
      .where(eq(decks.userId, userId));

    return Response.json({ decks: userDecks });
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('API Error:', error);
    return Response.json({ error: 'Internal server error' }, { status: 500 });
  }
}
```

### ✅ Resource-Specific Routes (with ID params)
```typescript
export async function GET(
  request: Request,
  { params }: { params: { deckId: string } }
) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) {
    return Response.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 });
  }

  try {
    // Always verify ownership
    const [deck] = await db.select()
      .from(decks)
      .where(and(
        eq(decks.id, params.deckId),
        eq(decks.userId, userId)
      ));

    if (!deck) {
      return Response.json({ error: 'Deck not found' }, { status: 404 });
    }

    return Response.json({ deck });
  } catch (error) {
    return Response.json({ error: 'Internal server error' }, { status: 500 });
  }
}
```

## Server Actions Patterns

### ✅ Form-based Server Actions
```typescript
'use server'

import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs';
import { revalidatePath, redirect } from 'next/navigation';
import { db } from '@/db';
import { decks } from '@/db/schema';

export async function createDeckAction(formData: FormData) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) {
    redirect('/sign-in');
  }

  const title = formData.get('title') as string;
  const description = formData.get('description') as string;

  if (!title?.trim()) {
    return { error: 'Title is required' };
  }

  try {
    const [newDeck] = await db.insert(decks)
      .values({
        title: title.trim(),
        description: description?.trim() || null,
        userId, // Critical: Always set userId
      })
      .returning();

    revalidatePath('/dashboard');
    return { success: true, deck: newDeck };
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Create deck error:', error);
    return { error: 'Failed to create deck' };
  }
}
```

### ✅ Typed Server Actions
```typescript
export async function updateDeckAction(deckId: string, data: { title: string; description?: string }) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) {
    throw new Error('Unauthorized');
  }

  // Verify ownership first
  const [existingDeck] = await db.select()
    .from(decks)
    .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.userId, userId)));

  if (!existingDeck) {
    throw new Error('Deck not found or access denied');
  }

  const [updatedDeck] = await db.update(decks)
    .set({
      title: data.title.trim(),
      description: data.description?.trim() || null,
      updatedAt: new Date(),
    })
    .where(eq(decks.id, deckId))
    .returning();

  revalidatePath('/dashboard');
  revalidatePath(`/deck/${deckId}`);
  return updatedDeck;
}
```

## Error Handling Standards

### ✅ Consistent Error Responses
```typescript
// API Routes
if (!userId) {
  return Response.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 });
}

if (!resource) {
  return Response.json({ error: 'Resource not found' }, { status: 404 });
}

// Server Actions
if (!userId) {
  return { error: 'Authentication required' };
  // OR redirect('/sign-in') for form actions
}

if (!resource) {
  return { error: 'Resource not found or access denied' };
}
```

## Input Validation

### ✅ Always Validate Input Data
```typescript
export async function POST(request: Request) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) {
    return Response.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 });
  }

  const body = await request.json();
  
  // Validate required fields
  if (!body.title?.trim()) {
    return Response.json({ error: 'Title is required' }, { status: 400 });
  }

  if (body.title.length > 100) {
    return Response.json({ error: 'Title too long' }, { status: 400 });
  }

  // Safe to proceed
  const [newDeck] = await db.insert(decks)
    .values({
      title: body.title.trim(),
      description: body.description?.trim() || null,
      userId,
    })
    .returning();

  return Response.json({ deck: newDeck });
}
```

## Security Checklist for Each Route/Action

- [ ] `auth()` called and `userId` extracted
- [ ] Early return for unauthenticated users (401/redirect)
- [ ] User ownership verified for resource operations
- [ ] Input validation for all user data
- [ ] `userId` included in all INSERT operations
- [ ] Appropriate error handling (don't leak internal details)
- [ ] `revalidatePath()` called after mutations
- [ ] Database errors caught and handled gracefully